All containers/elements for the selected version and action type are shown.
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
-<HattrickData>
-<MatchList>
-<Match>
<MatchID> : unsigned Integer
The globally unique identifier of the match.
</MatchID>
<MatchType> : MatchTypeID
Integer defining the type of match.
</MatchType>
<SourceSystem> : sourceSystem
Specifies which source system the match belongs to, this replace the old isYouth param
</SourceSystem>
<MatchDate> : DateTime
The start date (kick-off) of the match.
</MatchDate>
-<HomeTeam>
<HomeTeamID> : Integer
The teamID of the Home team in the match. (Negative for street teams)
</HomeTeamID>
<HomeTeamName> : String
The team name of the Home team in the match.
</HomeTeamName>
<HomeTeamShortName> : String
The short team name of the Home team in the match.
</HomeTeamShortName>
-<StartingLineup>
-<Player>
<PlayerID> : unsigned Integer
Globally unique ID of the player.
</PlayerID>
<RoleID> : MatchRoleID
An integer indicating which formal 'slot' (Role) the player has filled in the match.
</RoleID>
<PlayerName> : String
The full name of the player.
</PlayerName>
<Behaviour> : MatchBehaviourID
An integer indicating the individual order or repositioning that the player has played with. Not provided for Captain and Set Pieces taker.
</Behaviour>
</Player>
</StartingLineup>
</HomeTeam>
-<AwayTeam>
<AwayTeamID> : Integer
The teamID of the Away team in the match. (Negative for street teams)
</AwayTeamID>
<AwayTeamName> : String
The team name of the Away team in the match.
</AwayTeamName>
<AwayTeamShortName> : String
The short team name of the Away team in the match.
</AwayTeamShortName>
-<StartingLineup>
-<Player>
<PlayerID> : unsigned Integer
Globally unique ID of the player.
</PlayerID>
<RoleID> : MatchRoleID
An integer indicating which formal 'slot' (Role) the player has filled in the match.
</RoleID>
<PlayerName> : String
The full name of the player.
</PlayerName>
<Behaviour> : MatchBehaviourID
An integer indicating the individual order or repositioning that the player has played with. Not provided for Captain and Set Pieces taker.
</Behaviour>
</Player>
</StartingLineup>
</AwayTeam>
-<Substitutions>
-<Substitution>
<TeamID> : unsigned Integer
The globally unique TeamID for which the orders were sent.
</TeamID>
<SubjectPlayerID> : unsigned Integer
If a/ substitution: The player leaving. If b/ behaviour change: The player changing his behaviour. Or c/ position swap: the first player that will change his position.
</SubjectPlayerID>
<ObjectPlayerID> : unsigned Integer
The player entering (or once more the player changing behaviour). Or if position swap, the player to swap with.
</ObjectPlayerID>
<OrderType> : matchOrderTypeID
The type of the order.
</OrderType>
<NewPositionId> : MatchRoleID
An integer representing the new position for the (entering or staying) player.
</NewPositionId>
<NewPositionBehaviour> : MatchBehaviourID
An integer representing the new behaviour for the (entering or staying) player.
</NewPositionBehaviour>
<MatchMinute> : unsigned Integer
An integer indicating in which minute the order was executed.
</MatchMinute>
<MatchPart> : matchPart
Which part of the match the order was executed.
</MatchPart>
</Substitution>
</Substitutions>
-<EventList>
-<Event Index='unsigned Integer'>
<Minute> : unsigned Integer
The match minute when the event happened.
</Minute>
<MatchPart> : matchPart
Which part of the match the event happened.
</MatchPart>
<EventKey> : String
A unique key defining what type of event it was.
</EventKey>
<EventText> : String
String describing the event as it would appear in the match report.
</EventText>
<SubjectTeamID> : unsigned Integer
Integer that, for goals and chances, is indicating the attacking team. For other event, this field usually indicates the team that is doing something. It may indicate other things for other events - exactly what is not documented here and the SubjectTeamID information, while free to use for CHPPs is 'unsupported' and used 'at your own risk'.
</SubjectTeamID>
<SubjectPlayerID> : unsigned Integer
Integer that, for goals and chances, is indicating the scorer or the player failing to score. For other events, this field usually indicates the primarily active player. It may indicate other things for other events and like SubjectTeamID is 'unsupported' and used 'at your own risk'.
</SubjectPlayerID>
<ObjectPlayerID> : unsigned Integer
Integer that, for regular goals and chances, is indicating the defending team's goal keeper. For special event chances/goals, the ObjectPlayer is often the assisting player of the attacking team, but can be any other player that is involved in the event. For other events, this field is used very freely and can indicate any kind of relevant integer data. Like SubjectPlayerID and SubjectTeamID, it is 'unsupported' and used at 'your own risk'.
</ObjectPlayerID>
</Event>
</EventList>
<HomeGoals> : unsigned Integer
The current number of goals in the match for the home team.
</HomeGoals>
<AwayGoals> : unsigned Integer
The current number of goals in the match for the away team.
</AwayGoals>
<LastShownEventIndex> : unsigned Integer
The last shown event. Use this as LastShownIndexes for actionType=viewNew.
</LastShownEventIndex>
<NextEventMinute> : unsigned Integer
The minute that the next matchevent will happen, this allows you to only ask for new events when needed. Only available while the match is ongoing. It should only be used by the application, it should NOT be shown to the users.
</NextEventMinute>
<NextEventMatchPart> : matchPart
The matchPart in which the next matchevent will happen, this allows you to only ask for new events when needed. Only available while the match is ongoing. It should only be used by the application, it should NOT be shown to the users.
</NextEventMatchPart>
</Match>
</MatchList>
</HattrickData>
